   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1836-03_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1836-03-04"/>March 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1836</dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>Gentlemen,</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               In consequence of your letter of Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> <del></del><lb/>
               informing me that you now wish for <choice><orig>correc<lb/>
               =tions</orig><reg>corrections</reg></choice> for <title ref="./Workography.xml#Harry1">Harry and Lucy concluded</title>, for a<lb/>
               new Edition. I have sent a corrected copy of<lb/>
               the book for you to my sister <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Lestock Wilson</persName><lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#North-Audley-Street-1_ENK">N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>.1 North Audley Street</placeName><lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               You will be so good as to go to her <add>&amp; she will give it to you</add><lb/>
               and she having consulted <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Captain <choice><orig>Beau<lb/>
               fort</orig><reg>Beaufort</reg></choice></persName> will tell you what we wish to have done<lb/>
               respecting the line engravings proposed,<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               I have spared no labor in looking<lb/>
               over the 4 volumes page by page to consider<lb/>
               whether I could as you <del></del><add><unclear>desire</unclear></add> "divide the<lb/>
               work into chapters or sections with heads<lb/>
               of the principal subjects" - I have marked<lb/>
               the divisions <del>into sections <unclear>and so,</unclear></del> which<lb/>
               I <del>think best, and</del> <add>approve &amp; given</add> the best running titles<lb/>
               which I could devise. - But <del>I have the it to</del><lb/>
               <del><persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Mrs. L Wilson</persName> to decide</del> whether <add>all or</add> any of these<lb/>
               should be used or any <del>further</del> divisions be<lb/>
               made further than what are in <add>the</add> present <choice><orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi></orig><reg>Edition</reg></choice><lb/>
               I leave it to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Mrs L Wilson</persName> to decide - that<lb/>
               is to say as far as you are so obliging as<lb/>
               to leave the decision to me - you possess<lb/>
               the property in the work &amp; of course have the<lb/>
               sole right to decide <add>on all these points.</add> I thank you for consulting<lb/>
               me &amp; in return my friends &amp; I have given<lb/>
               the most careful attention to your suggestions<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1836-03_page02.jpg"/>
               with a view to accomplish your objects<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               You are so good as to say you " will<lb/>
               "be happy to discharge your obligation to me<lb/>
               for my trouble" - All the remuneration<lb/>
               I <del></del> require or would accept is a<lb/>
               few copies (say 6) of the new <choice><orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>.</orig><reg>Edition</reg></choice> for the<lb/>
               friends who have assisted me<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I am <choice><orig>Gent<hi rend="superscript">n</hi></orig><reg>Gentlemen</reg></choice> your <choice><orig>Obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</orig><reg>Obedient</reg></choice> <choice><orig>Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></orig><reg>Servant</reg></choice><lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">M E</persName><lb/>
            </closer>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>1836 March 4<hi rend="superscript">h</hi></addrLine><lb/>
                  <addrLine>copy - to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldX2">Baldwin</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CradX1">Cradock</persName></addrLine><lb/>
                  <addrLine>new <choice><orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi></orig><reg>Edition</reg></choice> of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Harry1">Harry &amp; Lucy</title></addrLine><lb/>
               </address>
            </closer>
